<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7238> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7238" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator, witness to an SC in 44. The nomen given as # in Josephus (AJ 14.220) was surely Quinctius. The tribe is given as # or #; read Pol. or Pub. (TJC) Badian would identify him with the # (ca. 16 letters) # in the SC de Panamareis (Gnomon 33, 1961, 496; Historia 12, 1963, 137-138; accepted by Sherk, RDGE no. 127, p. 162, taking Plancinus as a more probable equivalent for the Greek cognomen than Palicanus). Cf. M. Lollius Palikanus (20), above. See Wiseman, NM 237, no. 231.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7238 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7092> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7092" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The monetalis Palikanus, whose denarii with a tribune's bench or a curule chair on the reverse are now dated by Crawford (RRC 1.482, no. 473) to 45 (to 47 by others, MRR 2.444), may perhaps be identified with L. Lollius, a governor named on coins of Crete and Cyrenaica about 35 (so E. S. G. Robinson, BMC Catalogue, Cyrenaica, cciii, ccvii, 1141; cf. Grant, FITA 54-58), with more probability than with the senator, - f. Pob. Pallakeinos, whose name is partially preserved in the SC de Panamareis of 39, as suggested by TIC. See below, on M. Quinctius Plancinus (51), and Badian, Gnomon 33, 1961, 496; Historia 12, 1963, 137. He was earlier identified with Palikanus named on an aes coinage issued later than the Augustan reorganization of 23 (see G. Perl, Kho 52, 1970, 319-354, esp. 350; cf. MRR 2.498).\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7092 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6939> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6939" ;
